Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.30,0:00:40.60,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Only the light of deductions can cut through dark shadows and gloomy darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.60,0:00:44.09,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Find the confidential data in Aso and Kumamoto, the country of fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.09,0:00:45.64,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth\Nfor what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.64,0:00:47.90,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid\Nbut has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.90,0:00:50.32,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!{EDIT END TIME?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.64,0:02:33.78,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We, the Detective Boys, came to Kumamoto with Ran and old man Kogoro for a sightseeing trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.82,0:02:40.51,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Kumamoto is filled with many water sources, and is said to be the city with the best groundwater in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.21,0:02:46.57,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Here, you can get mineral water from the ordinary water supply.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.61,0:02:50.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's tasty!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.67,0:02:51.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.11,0:02:56.98,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But the most famous thing about Kumamoto is...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.98,0:02:59.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akaushi steaks and horsemeat!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.05,0:03:02.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention karashi renkon!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.03,0:03:05.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's so many great side dishes to go with a sip of kuma shochu...!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.89,0:03:09.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No, I wasn't talking about food...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.21,0:03:13.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd like some nice healthy taipien!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.65,0:03:17.94,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Anyway, the most famous thing about Kumamoto is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.94,0:03:19.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.88,0:03:21.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Mt Aso!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.74,0:03:28.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yup, Kumamoto is known not only as the capital of water, but also as the country of fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.00,0:03:33.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before we go and look at the crater,\Nlet's go and learn about volcanoes here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.38,0:03:40.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoa! Awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.61,0:03:44.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that he's here, Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s\Nenjoying it more than any of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.37,0:03:48.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mt. Aso is actually\Njust a nickname, and officially...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.89,0:03:49.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takadake...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.95,0:03:51.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nakadake...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.75,0:03:53.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nekodake...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.46,0:03:55.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eboshidake...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.25,0:03:56.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and Kijimadake...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.96,0:04:00.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...make up the\NFive Aso Mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.76,0:04:04.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the crater we're going to see later is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.28,0:04:05.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nakadake.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.67,0:04:12.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.13,0:04:14.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you okay, little boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.96,0:04:16.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.67,0:04:18.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But don't call me a little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.84,0:04:22.90,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Justin Takamori (7)\NTourist
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.51,0:04:20.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Justin!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.92,0:04:22.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name is Justin Takamori.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.27,0:04:24.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Justin?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.59,0:04:26.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're so cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.95,0:04:28.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, everybody says that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.33,0:04:33.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you're even cuter than me, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.21,0:04:38.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That smile...! That wink...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.53,0:04:42.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He knows exactly how to act\Nto get whatever he wants!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.46,0:04:44.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like you've got a rival.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.30,0:04:48.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you're still just number two.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.74,0:04:50.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then who's number one?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.66,0:04:52.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My mummy, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.96,0:04:53.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Justin!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.98,0:04:57.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought I told you not to walk off by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.04,0:04:57.98,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Jessica Takamori (30)\NJustin's Mother
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.01,0:05:02.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Mummy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.59,0:05:03.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.59,0:05:06.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got something good to show you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.15,0:05:08.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something good?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.14,0:05:14.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoa, awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.52,0:05:17.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've really got a lot of stamps.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.21,0:05:18.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.54,0:05:21.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's still a kid in that respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.28,0:05:24.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And an unpleasant one at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.17,0:05:25.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say something?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.95,0:05:27.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.37,0:05:28.68,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Now {\i1}you're{\i0} acting like a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.68,0:05:32.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really do have a very cute son.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.20,0:05:33.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Thank you{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.03,0:05:35.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me introduce myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.46,0:05:38.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm a detective, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.54,0:05:41.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My card... My card...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.30,0:05:42.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.50,0:05:46.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are those shiny cards...?\NWhere are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.83,0:05:51.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We should get going, Justin.\NSay goodbye to your friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.10,0:05:53.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, Mummy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.45,0:05:54.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.50,0:06:01.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here they are! Have a look at this...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.73,0:06:08.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you doing, Dad?\NWe're leaving!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.14,0:06:09.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.20,0:06:13.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next, we're finally gonna see the crater!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.06,0:06:29.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is better than I thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.44,0:06:31.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's really breathtaking!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.35,0:06:42.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't get to see a crater like this every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.05,0:06:43.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're really lucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.50,0:06:45.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Why's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.44,0:06:48.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because Nakadake is an active volcano.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.12,0:06:54.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At times, it releases poisonous gases,\Nand has to be closed off.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.90,0:06:56.68,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.68,0:07:00.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Just seeing this makes\Nthe whole trip here worthwhile.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.34,0:07:05.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They've got all sorts of animals here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.15,0:07:06.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.05,0:07:06.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.99,0:07:10.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kumamon stuffed toys!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.30,0:07:12.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can I go have a look?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.74,0:07:16.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure. But if you buy souvenirs now, you'll end up carrying them everywhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.66,0:07:18.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so let's get them when we're leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.02,0:07:19.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.69,0:07:20.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.17,0:07:22.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kuma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Kuma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.90,0:07:27.28,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But we'll just end up forgetting again, won't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.47,0:07:33.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look! Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.90,0:07:36.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're begging for food!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.47,0:07:45.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go! Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.71,0:08:29.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ahh, I'm stuffed!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.67,0:08:32.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see you've still got that good appetite.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.93,0:08:34.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.66,0:08:44.04,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Jun Kouda (26)\NKumamoto Police Detective
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.27,0:08:44.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A man just took the bag and left behind a Kumamon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.04,0:08:48.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Roger. We'll arrest him when he's somewhere more isolated.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.04,0:08:50.38,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Keiji Kosugi (41)\NKumamoto Police Detective
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.36,0:08:49.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ensure that you—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.08,0:08:49.98,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.38,0:08:52.28,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Namie Kajiyama (28)\NKumamoto Police Detective
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.84,0:08:51.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A girl just...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.63,0:08:52.28,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.28,0:08:53.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.13,0:08:56.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is yours, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.72,0:08:57.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.55,0:08:59.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.60,0:09:07.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.24,0:09:14.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You won't get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.02,0:09:25.96,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That cheeky kid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.96,0:09:27.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Move it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.04,0:09:28.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Watch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.11,0:09:30.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mummy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.18,0:09:37.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Justin! Justin!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.89,0:09:40.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.42,0:09:50.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.17,0:09:52.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You again, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.61,0:09:55.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Justin, did you hurt yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.80,0:09:58.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.21,0:09:59.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lawn gave me a soft landing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.82,0:10:01.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Glad to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.02,0:10:07.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's my Kumamon?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.37,0:10:10.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without it, my company...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.36,0:10:14.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My company's done for. {uso alt: my company is done for}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.40,0:10:15.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.62,0:10:16.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.31,0:10:19.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here. You'll be fine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.38,0:10:20.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.74,0:10:25.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What should I do? If I don't get it back...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.86,0:10:28.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What exactly happened here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.14,0:10:31.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you that girl's guardian?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.38,0:10:33.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, something like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.37,0:10:37.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me introduce myself. Have a look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.63,0:10:40.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kogoro Mouri...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.70,0:10:43.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you're that Great Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.89,0:10:47.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems like I got in the way of your investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.35,0:10:52.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you wouldn't mind, could you tell me about the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.04,0:11:04.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is, a thief broke into my company,\NKumamon Foods, two days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.78,0:11:07.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kumamon Foods?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.66,0:11:09.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kumamon...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.80,0:11:14.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name is Monkichi Kumada. Kumamon for short.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.86,0:11:17.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a nickname I've had ever since I was a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.78,0:11:22.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. So he's the original Kumamon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.65,0:11:25.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Director, you wanted to see me...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.19,0:11:26.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're late, Inoue!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.66,0:11:28.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.23,0:11:30.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why are the police here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.12,0:11:32.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I called them here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.48,0:11:37.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But never mind that,\Nyou tell this man about the break-in.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.77,0:11:38.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.50,0:11:46.46,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Mitsuo Inoue (32)\NKumamon Foods Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.54,0:11:41.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I arrived at work that morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.34,0:11:43.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the lock on the door had been broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.54,0:11:46.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I rushed inside to check on things,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.45,0:11:50.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but nothing seemed to be damaged,\Nso I let out a sigh of relief...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.55,0:11:54.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But my stuffed Kumamon was missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.96,0:11:56.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kumamon's Kumamon...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.17,0:11:59.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that's not all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.56,0:12:02.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something didn't quite seem right,\Nso I checked inside the desk,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.48,0:12:07.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the USB memory stick\Nwith our confidential data had vanished.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.87,0:12:11.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was development data\Non the new sensations and tastes
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.93,0:12:16.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,of completely new types of sweets\Nwe designed all by ourselves...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.50,0:12:19.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And we haven't patented them yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.20,0:12:23.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We may be a small company, but we've\Nbeen developing lots of new products
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.67,0:12:25.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and making money\Nfrom selling the patents.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.46,0:12:29.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if our competitors\Ngot hold of that data...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.42,0:12:36.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'd be doomed if it went somewhere like\Nthe industry leader, Higo Foods!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.06,0:12:38.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the thief contacted you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.53,0:12:39.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.83,0:12:43.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The next day,\NI got a call from the thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.06,0:12:49.44,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'll let you have the USB memory stick with\Nyour all-important data for only ¥10,000,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.44,0:12:54.00,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But if you tell the police,\Nthe deal's off. Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.86,0:12:57.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So today was the day\Nof the exchange?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.78,0:12:59.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.00,0:13:04.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said that he'd put the USB memory stick with\Nthe confidential data inside a stuffed Kumamon
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.72,0:13:07.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and trade it for a bag\Ncontaining ¥10,000,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.46,0:13:11.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would the thief go\Nthrough all that trouble?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.67,0:13:14.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably did it\Njust to spite me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.73,0:13:16.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What should we do, Director?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.46,0:13:21.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't the thief say the deal was off\Nif you told the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.02,0:13:22.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.34,0:13:25.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police told me\Nthey'd catch the thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.82,0:13:26.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet still...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.35,0:13:35.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kouda here. We've arrested\Nthe fleeing suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.12,0:13:37.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We also recovered the stuffed toy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.43,0:13:39.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. Good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.24,0:13:41.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't look so good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.78,0:13:42.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is your wound hurting again?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.88,0:13:44.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wound?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.83,0:13:48.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Kouda was stabbed\Nby a thug and hospitalized.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.51,0:13:50.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He only left the hospital yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.43,0:13:53.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's not important.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.26,0:13:59.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We couldn't find the USB memory stick\Nanywhere in the stuffed toy he was carrying.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.72,0:14:00.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.73,0:14:01.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.43,0:14:04.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't have it with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.57,0:14:06.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we couldn't find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.47,0:14:13.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, he claims that he was just asked\Nby someone he met at a bar to swap the toy for a bag,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.65,0:14:15.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and knows nothing about the theft.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.66,0:14:18.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he knows what\Nthe thief looks like, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.96,0:14:23.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said that he was wearing sunglasses\Nand a mask, so he never saw his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.47,0:14:24.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.46,0:14:32.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe his plan was just to get the ¥10,000,000, and he never put the USB memory stick in the toy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.85,0:14:35.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Ms. Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.10,0:14:39.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the man was running away, he crashed into a young boy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.63,0:14:42.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right... a cute half-Japanese boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.48,0:14:46.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That boy was carrying\Na stuffed Kumamon too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.88,0:14:52.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So maybe they got mixed up\Nwhen they collided?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.29,0:14:54.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is he right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.33,0:14:55.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.17,0:14:58.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a half-Japanese boy\Nand his foreign mother there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.96,0:15:02.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, then find them right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.37,0:15:05.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we don't have any\Nclues to find them...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.46,0:15:08.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well actually, we know that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.94,0:15:10.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name's Justin.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.99,0:15:13.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you know\Nwhere they were headed?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.23,0:15:15.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.64,0:15:19.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Justin had a stamp book.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.08,0:15:22.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So maybe he went somewhere\Nhe can get it stamped?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.12,0:15:28.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there are a lot of tourist attractions\Nwith stamps around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.52,0:15:35.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he showed us his stamp book\Nat the Aso Volcano Museum.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.91,0:15:42.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He already had stamps for Aso Ropeway\Nand Aso Farm Land at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.82,0:15:45.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I think we can\Nexclude those two.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.38,0:15:46.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.57,0:15:52.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so the closest tourist attraction other than\Nthose two would be Aso Shrine, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.59,0:15:56.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do they have a stamp there?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.08,0:15:58.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.23,0:15:59.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm a bit shocked though.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.94,0:16:02.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've got amazing memory\Nand observation skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.68,0:16:03.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do I?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.21,0:16:09.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, Kajiyama, you and\Nthat boy should head to Aso Shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.30,0:16:12.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go to Kumamon Foods\Nwith Director Kumada.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.41,0:16:16.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thief may attempt further contact.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.14,0:16:17.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.63,0:16:21.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.16,0:16:26.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How... did I get\Nmyself into this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.17,0:16:30.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really want to find\NJustin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.44,0:16:32.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's my fault\Nthat he got involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.53,0:16:35.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You haven't done anything wrong, Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.26,0:16:37.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right! Don't worry about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.45,0:16:41.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we let this case go, it'd be\Na blot on the Detective Boys' name!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.45,0:16:43.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.99,0:16:46.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll take responsibility for the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.62,0:16:48.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please hurry to Aso Shrine!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.73,0:16:49.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.95,0:17:04.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A half-Japanese boy and his foreign mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.08,0:17:06.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, they were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.77,0:17:09.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You sure, mister?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.08,0:17:13.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. He used the stamp here\Nabout an hour ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.79,0:17:16.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's Justin for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.01,0:17:16.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.78,0:17:20.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did they happen to say\Nwhere they were headed next?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.87,0:17:22.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm... I think he\Nsaid something like...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.68,0:17:28.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want to go and see\Nthe big pig falling asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.47,0:17:31.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The big pig falling asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.69,0:17:36.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a big black pig\Nat Aso Milk Farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.34,0:17:38.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's usually always sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.32,0:17:39.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, that's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.27,0:17:40.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.53,0:17:42.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have a look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.36,0:17:47.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we follow Justin's\Nroute so far...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.60,0:17:49.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aso Volcano Museum...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.59,0:17:51.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cuddly Dominion...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.13,0:17:52.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aso Shrine...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.25,0:17:54.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's heading north.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.04,0:17:58.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Aso Milk Farm is\Nover to the southwest, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.55,0:17:59.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.99,0:18:02.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you see it on a map,\Nit's a complete U-turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.62,0:18:07.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, Aso Milk Farm\Nis only open until 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.77,0:18:10.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}, what time is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.71,0:18:13.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's 3:40.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.06,0:18:18.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's quite far away,\Nso even if he left an hour ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.27,0:18:21.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he might not make it\Nbefore they close.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.61,0:18:26.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And whether he did or not,\Nit'd be closed for sure when we get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.03,0:18:29.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's El Patio Ranch\Nto the north...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.75,0:18:32.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I don't think\Nthey've ever had any pigs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.42,0:18:37.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only other main tourist\Nattractions to the north are...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.02,0:18:40.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kokuzo Shrine and Daikanbo...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.59,0:18:43.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Daikanbo?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.09,0:18:44.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.93,0:18:49.94,Signs,,0,0,0,,buta = pig
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.93,0:18:49.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Justin didn't say a big pig, he said a big Buddha!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.94,0:18:51.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's a Buddha?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.77,0:18:55.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's how you say {\i1}hotoke-sama{\i0} in English.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.64,0:18:58.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Justin's mother is a foreigner.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.81,0:19:00.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She probably taught him\Nthe name Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.91,0:19:04.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A big Buddha falling asleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.15,0:19:05.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.55,0:19:10.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The image of the sleeping Buddha made by\NMt Aso when seen from Daikanbo.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.67,0:19:17.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kosugi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, we figured out\Nthe boy's whereabouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.10,0:19:18.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's at Daikanbo.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.39,0:19:22.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, that's just what the brat says,\Nwe don't know for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.43,0:19:26.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel that I can\Ntrust his deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.05,0:19:38.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.44,0:19:40.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like a sleeping Buddha!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.53,0:19:45.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We better hurry up\Nand find Justin first.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.07,0:19:45.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.44,0:19:49.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No{\i0}! You can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.29,0:19:50.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That belongs to Justin!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.79,0:19:53.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you doing to my mummy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.68,0:19:55.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.50,0:19:57.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.37,0:20:02.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me go!\NWhat are you doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.78,0:20:21.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kajiyama!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.90,0:20:24.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kosugi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, follow that car!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.20,0:20:29.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thief kidnapped the boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.17,0:20:29.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.89,0:20:51.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably plans to hide\Nwhen he gets into Kumamoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.92,0:20:57.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kosugi here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.40,0:21:00.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Inoue, from Kumamon Foods.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.63,0:21:02.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We just got a call\Nfrom the thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.85,0:21:03.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.40,0:21:07.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you follow me,\NI'll kill the boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.02,0:21:11.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kajiyama.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.19,0:21:13.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The chase is off.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.46,0:21:14.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? But...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.20,0:21:18.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thief threatened\Nto kill the boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.29,0:21:21.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.42,0:21:23.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Justin...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.91,0:21:26.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was trying to save me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.37,0:21:30.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.\NI'm sure he'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.05,0:21:34.51,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.51,0:21:38.94,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}How did the thief know\Nthat Justin was at Daikanbo?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.94,0:21:46.45,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Actually, how did he know that Justin had\Nthe stuffed toy with the USB memory stick to begin with?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.45,0:21:51.32,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We didn't find out about the mix-up until\Nafter the fleeing man was arrested...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.32,0:21:54.27,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}...and the only ones\Nwho know about it are us,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.27,0:21:58.62,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Detectives Kosugi and Kajiyama\Nfrom the Kumamoto Police,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.62,0:22:00.91,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and Kumada{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} and Inoue{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}\Nfrom Kumamon Foods.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.91,0:22:07.75,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But when the thief kidnapped Justin,\NKumada{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} and Inoue{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} were at their company,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.75,0:22:10.61,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and we were at the scene,\Nand all have alibis...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.33,0:22:17.97,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Does that mean one of them\Nis working with the thief?
